{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "NGT [158] is an approximate nearest neighbor (ANN) search library developed by Yahoo Japan.",
    "It offers two construction methods: one extends KNN graphs with reverse edges, forming bi-directed KNN graphs [68], while the other incrementally builds graphs similar to HNSW with a range-based search strategy [130].",
    "In this study, we consider the former [68].",
    "Additionally, the library includes methods that employ quantization for highly efficient search.",
    "NGT maintains efficiency by pruning neighbors via RND and using Vantage-Point Trees [160] to select seed nodes for accurate query results."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
